It is clearly stated in problem that  each stone can reached from previous stone by making a jump of sizes (k - 1, k, k + 1),  where k is the step size to reach the previous stone, implies that for every stone we have three possibilities ignoring wheather the steps are valid or invalid.
This simply becomes our recursive cases/ calls from current stone where the frog is present.



Approaching to recursive Solution
