# Approach-3 Memoization + Binary Search (Optimized)

Now in the given question it is stated that list `stones` of are in ascending(***sorted***) order.

In recursive function we are linearly iterating and through each `stones` to find a `new_stone` which is equal to `curr_stone + prev_jump`.

Here we are applying $$Linear Search$$ instead of that we can apply $$Binary Search$$ to find out the `new_stone` as the given list of `stones` are in sorted Order.

# Code
<iframe src="https://leetcode.com/playground/7u5ma8TN/shared" frameBorder="0" width="1100" height="1000"></iframe>

