1. 0th index is always equal to zero.
2. 1st index must be one, because we are only allowed to make a jump of length 1 when we are at the 0th index.
3. If the above point satisfies we move on to find if we can reach the stone on the end index.

**Code Explanation:**
1. Recursion starts when we are standing at the 1st index and k=1 and we have 3 options [k-1,k,k+1] to make a jump.
2. `if i+j>i and helper(i+j,j):` Here we are ensuring the by making a jump we are only moving in the forward direction.
3. By making a jump of size (i+j) where j is (k-1) or k or (k+1) we must make sure that we land on a stone and not in water. So, We stored all the stones and its indeces in a dictionary to check if its a stone or not while landing.
4. If its not a stone we return False and go back. If it is a stone we continue.
5. Once we reach the final stone by any means thats it, we are done and we return True.  
