# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
on each stone we have the chance to choose the power by which we can jump and which possible stone to jump to.
And if we have choices to select, why not try to think in a Recursive way?
Remember the N-Queens problem?


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
from each stone we will try to jump with power = {power -1 or power or power + 1} as per the question stated, and try to reach any of the next stones
power here means 'k' from the question
we do this repeatedly untill the last index is found. 
If it cannot reach last index and is stuck at a stone, we go back and check from the previously stepped stone with a greater power


go through the comments and understand the code for better understanding

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
